Ask HN: How can I take charge of how software should work?
text:
For 1.5 years I’ve been assisting in the maintenance and enhancement of software that was built by a consultancy almost 3 years ago. No one on my team was part of the initial design, build, and launch. The documentation for the software is lacking and there is no one who I can go to to get confident feedback on how features should work.

Part of me want to leave the job cause it seems like a hopeless situation, but the pay is great. I want to turn the project around but that seems impossible cause there doesn’t appear to be a “true north”.

What can I do?

Show HN: Open-Source Notion UI, Lotion
text:
My friend and I love the Notion UI, so we open-source a version we have been building.

- Block-based editor - Drag to reorder blocks - Basic Markdown-parsing including bold, italic, headings and divider - Type '/' for command menu and shortcuts

Tiny fun detail: When you move between blocks with your arrow keys, your cursor will remain at roughly the same horizontal position (vs jumping to the start or end of a block).

Lotion is quite limited for now, and we would love any contributions (e.g. image blocks, video blocks, code blocks, etc.)

Ask HN: Where to find test Stripe data?
text:
Hello,

I'm working on an analytics tool for Stripe. Where can I find test Stripe datasets? I don't mind it being fake data, but it needs to follow real relationships to some extent. I have a small store that has some data, but it's not nearly big enough to generalize.

I did find https://github.com/stripe-samples/test-data and use that, but it's very limited.

Appreciate your help!

Where is it possible to raise capital [25k] through DeFi for real world?
text:
We've been working for the past months to establish a low risk business model, idealize and code a DAO governance perfectly aligned with what is, I think, to be the best of what crypto has to offer in the real world, equitability, financial inclusion and inclusive governance.

The financial business model is functioning well and very limited risk since we produce commodity. We are at the point of simply trying the whole process of the business with the first structure of our DAO governance plus raise capital through crypto, bring it in the real world and distribute the yield back in crypto.

We initially thought of making our own Pool of liquidity with rules according to what we need but there are many many laws to offer investment in the real world and the lawyer's costs are very expensive for the means we have atm.

Thus, we are asking ourselves, is there anyway to raise a certain sum of capital, 25k for now, then 10-20X this amount in 6 months without collateral in crypto.

I know of goldfinch.finance, but all their loans are over half a million to 10-15millions, which is not where we are at yet.

We can provide 20-40% apy on USD based on a low risk business model that can almost infinitely scale since we are in the commodity business.

Kind regards :)
